# Security Rules

- Follow OWASP Top 10 protections
- Never store secrets in code or settings.json -- use environment variables
- Validate all user input with Zod at system boundaries
- Use parameterized queries (Prisma handles this)
- Implement proper CSRF protection
- Set secure HTTP headers (Content-Security-Policy, etc.)
- Use NextAuth.js v5 for authentication -- never roll custom auth
- Apply principle of least privilege for API permissions
